{
  "texts": [
    "This pattern aligns with previous research showing mixed outcomes from LLMs in less-structured creative domains (Chen and Chan, 2024; Zhou and Lee, 2024; Doshi and Houser, 2024).",
    "Our analysis of heterogeneous effects further reveals that the disparity between innovation types is particularly pronounced in more active projects with extensive discussions and documentation.",
    "Projects with higher activity provide richer context for LLMs, amplifying their effectiveness for iterative innovation.",
    "This finding reinforces our explanation regarding the importance of detailed contextual information.",
    "Popular packages generate more bug reports, attract more discussions, and maintain better documentationall enhancing the context available to LLMs and increasing their utility for maintenance tasks."
  ]
}